WEBVTT

00:02.469 --> 00:03.303
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"NECESSARY ROUGHNESS"...</i>

00:04.104 --> 00:06.106
Nico: I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR FATHER.

00:06.139 --> 00:08.341
Juliette:
DADDY LEFT ME THE TEAM.

00:08.375 --> 00:11.077
COMMUNITY SERVICE, HUH?
BEEN THERE.

00:11.111 --> 00:13.346
NICO, YOU KEEP THAT GIRL
AWAY FROM MY SON.

00:13.380 --> 00:15.482
I'M HAVING TROUBLE
RESTARTING MY PRACTICE.

00:15.515 --> 00:19.119
IT'S A GOOD IDEA
THAT YOU SEE ME.

00:19.152 --> 00:20.420
T.K: YOU EVER THINK
SHE'S HITTING IT

00:20.453 --> 00:21.521
WITH SOMEBODY
IN THE ORGANIZATION?

00:21.554 --> 00:23.056
MY MONEY'S ON NICO.

00:23.490 --> 00:25.225
TOES SHOULD BE THE GUY
ON THE SIDELINES

00:25.258 --> 00:26.426
TRYING TO GET IN THE GAME,
NOT ME.

00:26.459 --> 00:28.094
RIP AND DIP.

00:28.128 --> 00:29.029
YOU'RE GONNA
TELL ME HOW TO PLAY FOOTBALL.

00:31.197 --> 00:32.265
ALL IT TOOK WAS
A LITTLE DIP, A LITTLE RIP,

00:32.298 --> 00:35.135
GET THAT EXTRA STEP I NEEDED,
AND THE REST IS HISTORY.

00:35.168 --> 00:37.237
GAME ON, DAWG.

00:37.270 --> 00:38.371
GAME ON.

00:40.440 --> 00:43.309
Man:
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

00:43.343 --> 00:47.180
TOGETHER FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN OVER A DECADE,

00:47.213 --> 00:52.519
PLEASE WELCOME VON DOZER!

00:52.552 --> 00:55.488
[ "BITTER SUGAR" PLAYS ]

00:55.522 --> 00:57.490
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

00:59.492 --> 01:03.263
* THE DAY WE MET,
THERE WAS NO DENYING *

01:03.296 --> 01:04.597
Dani:
<i>THE MYTH OF THE ROCK GOD --</i>

01:04.631 --> 01:06.599
<i>EDGY, GLAMOROUS,</i>
<i>LARGER-THAN-LIFE.</i>

01:06.633 --> 01:10.537
* YOU LOOKED SO SWEET,
LIKE A CHERRY SODA *

01:10.570 --> 01:12.539
<i>THE FACT IS WHETHER</i>
<i>WE'VE CHOSEN THEM OR NOT,</i>

01:12.572 --> 01:15.909
<i>WE ALL HAVE OUR OWN MYTHS</i>
<i>TO LIVE UP TO.</i>

01:15.942 --> 01:20.213
<i>THE QUESTION IS, IS IT POSSIBLE</i>
<i>TO SHATTER A MYTH,</i>

01:20.246 --> 01:22.449
<i>ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU'VE STARTED</i>
<i>TO BELIEVE IT YOURSELF?</i>

01:22.482 --> 01:27.287
* I KNEW THAT YOU
WOULD DRIVE ME CRAZY *

01:28.621 --> 01:31.591
* YOU TASTE LIKE

01:31.624 --> 01:35.195
* BITTER SUGAR

01:35.228 --> 01:38.298
* WE DO IT ALL NIGHT

01:38.331 --> 01:41.568
* JUST LIKE BITTER SUGAR

01:43.503 --> 01:44.537
WHOA!
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:44.571 --> 01:46.539
[ FEEDBACK ]

01:46.573 --> 01:50.343
OHH.

01:53.546 --> 01:55.648
[ SONG ENDS ]

01:55.682 --> 01:58.284
[<i>"BITTER SUGAR" PLAYS</i>]

02:02.322 --> 02:05.158
*<i>WHOA</i>*

02:09.462 --> 02:13.233
*<i>THE DAY WE MET,</i>
<i>THERE WAS NO DENYING</i>*

02:13.266 --> 02:16.603
*<i>I HAD TO HAVE YOU,</i>
<i>I JUST COULDN'T RESIST</i>*

02:16.636 --> 02:20.540
*<i>YOU LOOKED SO SWEET,</i>
<i>LIKE A CHERRY SODA</i>*

02:20.573 --> 02:23.543
*<i>IN HIGH HEELS</i>
<i>AND A BABY-DOLL DRESS</i>*

02:23.576 --> 02:25.679
OH! OH.
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

02:25.712 --> 02:28.314
OH, YEAH. WHAT'S UP?

02:28.348 --> 02:30.316
WHAT'S THAT RACKET,
MOM?

02:30.350 --> 02:33.319
VON DOZER --
THE BEST BAND...

02:33.353 --> 02:35.555
* EVER!

02:35.588 --> 02:36.389
[ LAUGHS ]

02:36.423 --> 02:39.559
WHERE ARE YOU OFF TO
SO NICEY-NICEY?

02:39.592 --> 02:42.462
IT'S THE FIRST DAY
OF MY NEW COMMUNITY SERVICE.

02:42.495 --> 02:45.632
YOU NEED A SPORTS COAT AND A TIE
TO PICK UP TRASH?

02:45.665 --> 02:48.668
ACTUALLY, I'M WORKING FOR
A CHARITY NOW -- HAWKS CARES.

02:48.702 --> 02:50.670
SINCE WHEN?

02:50.704 --> 02:54.274
SINCE...JULIETTE PITTMAN
HOOKED ME UP.

02:55.742 --> 02:57.277
SAY WHAT NOW?

02:57.310 --> 02:58.478
IT'S A GREAT ORGANIZATION.

02:58.511 --> 02:59.446
DO YOU KNOW
HOW MANY OF THESE KIDS

02:59.479 --> 03:01.648
GET A SOLID MEAL EVERY DAY
BECAUSE OF THEM?

03:01.681 --> 03:05.285
MOM, I'LL BE GAINING
INVALUABLE CORPORATE EXPERIENCE

03:05.318 --> 03:07.554
IN AN AIR-CONDITIONED
ENVIRONMENT.

03:07.587 --> 03:10.490
WITH JULIETTE PITTMAN.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.527
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA START
TRUSTING ME?

03:14.561 --> 03:16.629
[ SMOOCHES ]

03:16.663 --> 03:19.432
WHEN YOU STOP
GETTING ARRESTED!

03:22.635 --> 03:25.672
GENTLEMEN, OUR SEASON
IS OFF TO A GREAT START,

03:25.705 --> 03:28.708
AND AS SUCH, I'VE TAKEN IT
UPON MYSELF TO CREATE

03:28.742 --> 03:30.610
AN IMAGE WORTHY
OF THAT SUCCESS.

03:31.711 --> 03:35.348
I GIVE YOU...
THE NEW HAWK UNIFORM,

03:35.382 --> 03:36.649
DESIGNED BY MICHAEL KORS.

03:36.683 --> 03:38.685
[ SPITS ]
BOLD, ISN'T IT?

03:38.718 --> 03:40.520
THE OREGON DUCKS
WENT FASHION-FORWARD,

03:40.553 --> 03:42.622
AND THEY'RE MAKING A STATEMENT,
GETTING NOTICED,

03:42.655 --> 03:44.657
AND MOVING MERCHANDISE
IN A BIG WAY.

03:44.691 --> 03:47.894
I ALSO SET UP A PHOTO SHOOT
FOR THE COVER OF A MAGAZINE

03:47.927 --> 03:52.532
THAT SHALL REMAIN NAMELESS,
BUT LET'S JUST SAY IT'S BIG.

03:52.565 --> 03:56.536
I SOLD THEM ON MY IDEA TO MAKE
FOOTBALL NOT JUST COOL, BUT HOT.

03:56.569 --> 03:59.339
She's like
the freaking Weather Channel.

03:59.372 --> 04:01.775
Everything's "hot."

04:01.808 --> 04:05.645
I think I quit.

04:05.679 --> 04:07.080
THIS WASN'T
SUPPOSED TO HAPPEN.

04:07.113 --> 04:08.648
YOU PROMISED
THIS WOULDN'T HAPPEN.

04:08.682 --> 04:09.949
WHAT -- YOU'RE NOT A FAN
OF THE RED, WHITE, AND BLING?

04:09.983 --> 04:12.652
OH, COME ON.
THE LEAGUE IS NEVER
GONNA APPROVE THOSE UNIFORMS.

04:12.686 --> 04:13.653
AND THE PHOTO SHOOT --

04:13.687 --> 04:14.621
NICO,
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW

04:14.654 --> 04:16.556
THAT THIS IS JUST
THE TIP OF THE ICEBERG.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.758
THIS IS JUST GONNA
PLAY ITSELF OUT. TRUST ME.

04:18.792 --> 04:20.660
SHE'S GONNA FIND
SOMETHING MORE EXCITING TO DO --

04:20.694 --> 04:22.662
GET BORED.
WHY?

04:22.696 --> 04:25.465
'CAUSE
THAT'S WHAT WOMEN DO?

04:25.498 --> 04:27.701
NO, THAT'S
WHAT JULIETTE DOES.

04:27.734 --> 04:30.670
LOOK, I AM TRYING TO
RUN A TEAM.

04:30.704 --> 04:33.740
SHE JUST
LOST HER FATHER.

04:33.773 --> 04:35.775
HAVE SOME COMPASSION.

04:38.545 --> 04:41.948
Dani: SO, VON DOZER.

04:41.981 --> 04:45.685
DAVID, PAUL, WELCOME.

04:45.719 --> 04:48.788
TELL ME
WHY YOU ARE HERE TODAY.

04:48.822 --> 04:50.757
I THINK
PAUL REMINDS ME OF MY DAD,

04:50.790 --> 04:53.493
AND I'M TRANSFERRING
THE RESENTMENT I HAVE

04:53.526 --> 04:56.796
FOR DEAR OLD DICKHEAD
ON TO HIM.

04:56.830 --> 04:58.498
NO, THE PROBLEM IS
YOU DRINK TOO MUCH.

04:58.531 --> 04:59.599
YOU'RE
CHRONICALLY LATE.

04:59.632 --> 05:02.736
WHEN YOU DO SHOW UP,
YOU'RE DISTRACTED, HUNG OVER,

05:02.769 --> 05:04.971
AND MORE CONCERNED ABOUT
GETTING LAID THAN PLAYING MUSIC.

05:05.005 --> 05:08.408
SOUNDS LIKE ROCK 'N' ROLL,
DON'T YOU THINK, DR. SANTINO?

05:08.441 --> 05:12.545
HERE'S WHAT I KNOW --
UH, YOU TWO GREW UP TOGETHER,

05:12.579 --> 05:14.714
FORMED VON DOZER
WHILE STILL IN HIGH SCHOOL,

05:14.748 --> 05:17.450
FOUR PLATINUM RECORDS,
SOLD-OUT STADIUMS.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.552
AND WHILE OTHER BAND MEMBERS
HAVE COME AND GONE,

05:19.586 --> 05:21.721
YOU TWO HAVE BEEN
THE ONES TO STAY TOGETHER,

05:21.755 --> 05:24.624
UNTIL 10 YEARS AGO,
WHEN YOU BROKE UP.

05:24.657 --> 05:29.629
AND IF I UNDERSTAND CORRECTLY,
YOU HAVEN'T SPOKEN MUCH SINCE.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.998
DO I SMELL A DOZE-HEAD?

05:32.032 --> 05:36.636
LET'S JUST SAY THAT I AM...
FAMILIAR WITH YOUR WORK.

05:36.670 --> 05:40.573
WHAT MADE YOU DECIDE
TO DO THIS REUNION TOUR?

05:40.607 --> 05:43.009
THE CASH -- WE NEED IT.

05:43.043 --> 05:44.678
YEAH, WELL, AFTER WHAT
YOU PULLED LAST WEEK,

05:44.711 --> 05:46.579
TWO OTHER VENUES
ALREADY CANCELED,

05:46.613 --> 05:48.481
NOT TO MENTION
THE THREE PENDING LAWSUITS.

05:48.515 --> 05:50.617
SO WE'RE LOSING CASH,
NOT MAKING IT.

05:50.650 --> 05:52.752
[ As Scooby-Doo ] RUH-ROH!
I HAVE
TWO CHILDREN AT HOME.

05:52.786 --> 05:56.723
I DON'T NEED ANOTHER ONE --
WHO'S OUT OF CONTROL! --

05:56.756 --> 05:58.858
AS MY BUSINESS PARTNER.

06:00.894 --> 06:03.763
LET ME
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

06:03.797 --> 06:08.568
PEOPLE COME TO SEE OUR BAND
BECAUSE I'M OUT OF CONTROL!

06:08.601 --> 06:10.770
[ LAUGHS ]

06:10.804 --> 06:12.672
I AM THE SHOW, DUDE.

06:12.706 --> 06:15.575
THEY COME IN SPITE OF YOU, DUDE,
FOR THE MUSIC --

06:15.608 --> 06:17.444
MOST OF WHICH,
I'VE WRITTEN.

06:17.477 --> 06:21.648
OKAY, OBVIOUSLY
THERE IS SOME UNRESOLVED ANGER

06:21.681 --> 06:22.649
BETWEEN YOU,

06:22.682 --> 06:26.553
BUT ARE YOU BOTH COMMITTED
TO DOING THIS TOUR

06:26.586 --> 06:28.555
AND TO WORKING
ON THE RELATIONSHIP?

06:30.623 --> 06:32.592
I'M HERE, AREN'T I?

06:32.625 --> 06:35.495
DR. SANTINO, PLEASE HELP US
GET THROUGH THIS TOUR

06:35.528 --> 06:36.830
WITHOUT KILLING EACH OTHER.

06:38.765 --> 06:41.868
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

06:51.244 --> 06:54.180
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

06:54.214 --> 06:55.615
[ GASPS ] OH!

06:55.648 --> 06:58.184
AAH! NICO.

06:58.218 --> 06:59.085
[ SIGHS ]

06:59.119 --> 07:01.755
I THOUGHT WE WERE DONE
WITH THAT MOVE.

07:01.788 --> 07:04.657
SORRY. NO.

07:04.691 --> 07:05.658
WE NEED TO TALK.

07:05.692 --> 07:07.027
UH, IS IT T.K.?

07:07.060 --> 07:08.695
NO.

07:08.728 --> 07:10.663
ABOUT US.

07:10.697 --> 07:13.600
OH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:13.633 --> 07:15.035
WELL,
I THOUGHT THAT, UM --

07:15.068 --> 07:18.538
I THOUGHT WE WERE DONE
WITH THAT MOVE, TOO.

07:18.571 --> 07:20.707
NOT QUITE.

07:22.575 --> 07:24.778
[ MOANS ]

07:37.090 --> 07:38.625
[ FOGHORN BLARES ]

07:38.658 --> 07:40.794
WHA...?

07:40.827 --> 07:45.699
SO, I AM
OFFICIALLY DEFROSTED.

07:45.732 --> 07:49.069
I GAVE LITTLE DUDE
A PROPER FISH BURIAL,

07:49.102 --> 07:52.739
OFFICE BACK UP AND RUNNING --
SMOOTH SAILING, YEP, YEP, YEP.

07:52.772 --> 07:54.641
AND YET HERE YOU ARE.

07:54.674 --> 07:55.709
YEP.

07:55.742 --> 07:58.244
THAT LITTLE FOOT
JUST TWITCHING AWAY,

07:58.278 --> 08:02.315
INDICATING YOU WOULD LIKE TO
TALK TO ME ABOUT SOMETHING.

08:02.349 --> 08:04.617
BUT YOU'RE...

08:04.651 --> 08:05.719
STALLING.

08:05.752 --> 08:07.654
YEAH.

08:08.855 --> 08:13.727
I HAVE BEEN HAVING DREAMS
ABOUT A CO-WORKER.

08:13.760 --> 08:15.695
MATT OR NICO?

08:15.729 --> 08:17.697
I HAPPEN TO
HAVE A LOT OF CO-WORKERS,

08:17.731 --> 08:19.833
SO I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WOULD MAKE YOU --

08:19.866 --> 08:22.569
[ SIGHS ]
NICO.

08:22.602 --> 08:24.637
AND THE NATURE
OF THESE DREAMS?

08:24.671 --> 08:25.739
SEXUAL.

08:25.772 --> 08:27.841
WERE THEY
SATISFYING OR NOT?

08:27.874 --> 08:28.675
[ SIGHS ]

08:28.708 --> 08:30.944
THEY WERE
PRETTY DARN SATISFYING.

08:30.977 --> 08:32.712
OKAY.

08:32.746 --> 08:37.350
I REALIZE THAT SEX DREAMS
ARE NOT ABOUT...SEX,

08:37.384 --> 08:38.318
BUT I CAN'T FIGURE OUT

08:38.351 --> 08:41.855
WHAT THE CONNECTION IS
BETWEEN ALL OF THEM.

08:41.888 --> 08:45.759
THE LAST ONE
WAS ACTUALLY A SCENE

08:45.792 --> 08:47.727
FROM A LITTLE MOVIE
CALLED "TITANIC."

08:47.761 --> 08:48.661
[ LAUGHS ]

08:48.695 --> 08:51.364
YOU KNOW, WHEN THEY'RE
IN THE CARGO HOLD

08:51.398 --> 08:53.733
AND THEY'RE IN THE CAR AND
IT'S SUPER-STEAMY AND THE --

08:53.767 --> 08:55.735
WAS KATE WINSLET IN IT?

08:55.769 --> 08:57.671
HMM?
DiCAPRIO?

08:57.704 --> 09:00.740
EVERYBODY DIES
OR YOU DIE?

09:00.774 --> 09:01.708
NO.

09:01.741 --> 09:05.945
DR. GUNNER, IT, UH --
IT WAS JUST THE SEX.

09:05.979 --> 09:08.748
IT WAS JUST
THE SEX WITH A MAN

09:08.782 --> 09:12.786
THAT I SHOULD NEVER,
EVER HAVE SEX WITH.

09:17.791 --> 09:20.026
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

09:20.060 --> 09:22.862
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
JULIETTE.

09:22.896 --> 09:25.699
WHEREFORE ART THOU,
JULIETTE? [ LAUGHS ]

09:25.732 --> 09:27.634
I THINK SOMEBODY BOO-BOOED.

09:29.736 --> 09:30.737
OH, NO,
THAT'S THE RIGHT COSTUME.

09:30.770 --> 09:32.872
YOU'LL UNDERSTAND
WHEN YOU SEE THE WHOLE LAYOUT.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.709
I'M IN A ONESIE.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.944
IT LOOKS FANTASTIC.

09:37.977 --> 09:41.715
UH, IT'S ALL GOOD 'CAUSE I WAS
THINKING WE COULD, YOU KNOW,

09:41.748 --> 09:42.716
JUST CROP IT
RIGHT HERE ANYWAY

09:42.749 --> 09:44.384
'CAUSE THIS IS
WHERE THE MONEY IS, YOU KNOW?

09:44.417 --> 09:45.251
OH!

09:45.285 --> 09:46.186
WELL, I HOPE YOU
BROUGHT EXTRA CAMERAS

09:46.219 --> 09:48.788
'CAUSE THAT MUG'S
APT TO CRACK SOME LENSES.

09:48.822 --> 09:49.789
HEY.
HI.

09:49.823 --> 09:50.724
HEY, THERE.

09:50.757 --> 09:53.727
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:53.760 --> 09:55.762
TELL ME TOES IS LOST.

09:55.795 --> 09:56.996
NO,
IT'S ALL THREE OF US --

09:57.030 --> 09:59.866
ME AND MY TWO
STAR WIDE RECEIVERS.

09:59.899 --> 10:02.802
COME HERE.
STEP INTO MY OFFICE.

10:02.836 --> 10:04.938
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:04.971 --> 10:08.708
WHY DOES
TOES GET PINSTRIPES,

10:08.742 --> 10:10.810
AND I GET PEN STRIPES?

10:10.844 --> 10:12.746
WELL,
EVERYONE HAS AN IMAGE.

10:12.779 --> 10:14.948
TOES IS OUR GENTLEMAN,
AND YOU'RE OUR BAD BOY.

10:14.981 --> 10:17.450
AND I'M THE GIRL
CAUGHT IN THE MIDDLE.

10:17.484 --> 10:18.752
[ LAUGHS ]

10:18.785 --> 10:19.953
OKAY, I SMELL
WHAT YOU'RE COOKING,

10:19.986 --> 10:21.955
BUT I'M ORDERING
OFF THE MENU, OKAY?

10:21.988 --> 10:25.458
THE BAD-BOY MYTH --
NOT MY BAG ANYMORE.

10:25.492 --> 10:27.761
OH, OKAY.
I UNDERSTAND.

10:27.794 --> 10:30.030
I DON'T WANT YOU TO DO ANYTHING
THAT MAKES YOU UNCOMFORTABLE.

10:30.063 --> 10:33.233
THAT'S COOL. ALL RIGHT,
WHAT ARE MY OPTIONS?

10:33.266 --> 10:36.236
YOUR OPTIONS ARE...

10:36.269 --> 10:37.771
TO LEAVE.

10:37.804 --> 10:38.605
EXCUSE ME.

10:38.638 --> 10:41.975
[ LAUGHS ]
I THOUGHT YOU -- YOU...

10:42.008 --> 10:46.479
I WANT TO
STOMP A HOLE IN HIS FACE.

10:46.513 --> 10:49.115
I WANT TO PUT MY TOES
UP TOES' ASS.

10:49.149 --> 10:52.986
OKAY,
BUT WHAT YOU SHOULD DO IS...

10:53.019 --> 10:56.489
I KNOW --
BREATHE, RELAX,

10:56.523 --> 10:58.858
WORK DILIGENTLY
TO REGAIN MY SPOT.

10:58.892 --> 10:59.893
YEAH.

10:59.926 --> 11:03.797
DON'T LET TOES OR JULIETTE
DISTRACT YOU FROM THAT.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.799
[ SIGHS ]
THAT'S GREAT IN THEORY.

11:05.832 --> 11:07.834
IT'S JUST THAT
I'M TRYING TO FLY --

11:07.867 --> 11:09.135
TRYING TO REINVENT MYSELF,

11:09.169 --> 11:11.871
AND JULIETTE PITTMAN
IS LITERALLY HOLDING ME BACK

11:11.905 --> 11:12.806
WITH A BALL AND CHAIN.

11:12.839 --> 11:15.742
GOD,
GRANT ME THE SERENITY

11:15.775 --> 11:17.277
TO ACCEPT
THE THINGS I CANNOT CHANGE...

11:17.310 --> 11:19.012
...THE COURAGE
TO CHANGE THE THINGS THAT I CAN,

11:19.045 --> 11:21.881
AND THE WISDOM
TO KNOW THE DIFFERENCE.

11:21.915 --> 11:22.816
YEAH, I'M THINKING ABOUT

11:22.849 --> 11:24.818
GETTING IT TATTOOED
ACROSS MY FOREHEAD.

11:24.851 --> 11:30.857
TERRENCE, DON'T TELL EVERYBODY
WHAT A NEW MAN YOU ARE.

11:30.890 --> 11:32.092
<i>SHOW</i>THEM.

11:34.894 --> 11:36.296
[ SIGHS ]

11:36.329 --> 11:38.465
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

11:40.967 --> 11:42.869
HELLO.

11:42.902 --> 11:44.871
OHH!

11:44.904 --> 11:46.940
WHAT DO YOU GOT TO BE
SO SNEAKY FOR ALL THE TIME?

11:46.973 --> 11:50.010
WHEN I WAS A KID, I WAS ALWAYS
THE BEST AT HIDE-AND-SEEK.

11:50.043 --> 11:51.778
I'LL BET YOU WERE.

11:51.811 --> 11:52.612
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

11:52.645 --> 11:55.849
ARE YOU AWARE
THAT JULIETTE PITTMAN

11:55.882 --> 11:57.851
HAS OFFERED
RAY JAY A POSITION

11:57.884 --> 12:00.553
AT HAWKS CARES
FOR HIS COMMUNITY SERVICE?

12:00.587 --> 12:03.056
HMM. I AM NOW.

12:03.089 --> 12:05.825
I TAKE IT
YOU DON'T LIKE THIS.

12:05.859 --> 12:09.329
JULIETTE PITTMAN
ISN'T EXACTLY MOTHER TERESA.

12:09.362 --> 12:13.833
DANI, SHE HAS A GOOD HEART.
SHE'S JUST YOUNG.

12:13.867 --> 12:17.070
WELL, IT'S NOT HER HEART
THAT I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

12:17.103 --> 12:20.840
I'LL KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.
I PROMISE.

12:25.845 --> 12:27.814
Dani: THANK YOU.

12:27.847 --> 12:30.016
Paul:
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

12:30.050 --> 12:32.519
PLACE LOOKS
A LOT SMALLER NOW.

12:32.552 --> 12:34.821
MAYBE
YOU JUST GOT BIGGER.
YEAH.

12:34.854 --> 12:35.922
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:35.955 --> 12:38.825
SO YOU BROUGHT US HERE
BECAUSE...

12:38.858 --> 12:42.028
WELL, IF MY FAN-CLUB MEMORY
SERVES ME,

12:42.062 --> 12:46.132
THE ROUND ABOUT IS WHERE
IT ALL BEGAN FOR VON DOZER.

12:46.166 --> 12:48.935
SOMETIMES IT'S GOOD
TO REMEMBER WHERE YOU CAME FROM

12:48.968 --> 12:50.937
IN ORDER TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE YOU'RE GOING.

12:50.970 --> 12:54.941
OH!
I CANNOT BELIEVE THIS!

12:54.974 --> 12:56.543
IS THAT DAVID BLAIZE
ALL GROWN UP?

12:56.576 --> 12:58.845
HEY, PAUL,
HOW YOU DOING?

12:58.878 --> 12:59.846
GOOD.
YEAH?

12:59.879 --> 13:02.849
HOLY HELL, DIRTY DOUG.
HOW'S IT HANGING, MAN?

13:02.882 --> 13:04.150
WELL, IT AIN'T --
NOT WITHOUT MEDICATION.

13:04.184 --> 13:05.151
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:05.185 --> 13:07.620
WHAT'S IT BEEN --
15 YEARS NOW?

13:07.654 --> 13:09.923
[ LAUGHS ] SO,
WHAT THE HELL YOU DOING HERE?

13:09.956 --> 13:11.091
I MEAN,
YOU SHOULD HAVE CALLED.

13:11.124 --> 13:13.626
I COULD HAVE PACKED THE PLACE.
THERE'S ONLY 25 PEOPLE HERE.

13:13.660 --> 13:14.627
WELL,
IT'S ABOUT 25 MORE

13:14.661 --> 13:17.130
THAN WHEN WE GIGGED HERE
THE FIRST TIME, RIGHT?

13:17.163 --> 13:19.966
YOU HERE TO JAM?

13:22.669 --> 13:26.940
HEY, DOC, HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT
YOUR OWN PRIVATE CONCERT?

13:26.973 --> 13:29.642
ME? AWESOME!

13:29.676 --> 13:30.877
[ LAUGHS ]

13:33.913 --> 13:34.981
A BOTTLE OF
YOUR FINEST BUBBLY, PLEASE.

13:35.015 --> 13:37.083
MAKE THAT TWO.

13:37.117 --> 13:41.221
ACTUALLY, I-I'LL
HAVE BUBBLY...WATER.

13:41.254 --> 13:43.223
OH,
YOU'RE DOING THAT?

13:43.256 --> 13:45.959
YEAH.
FRESH OUT OF REHAB.

13:45.992 --> 13:48.194
I WENT TO REHAB.
YOU GET THE BEST DRUGS THERE.

13:49.929 --> 13:52.165
KIDDING. SORT OF.

13:52.198 --> 13:53.166
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:53.199 --> 13:54.968
YEAH, I'M JUST TRYING TO
STICK WITH THE PROGRAM,

13:55.001 --> 13:56.970
YOU KNOW, UH,
REINVENT MYSELF.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.672
SO YOU
DIDN'T BRING ME HERE

13:58.705 --> 14:01.074
TO GET ME DRUNK, NAKED,
AND X-RATED?

14:01.107 --> 14:04.678
UNFORTUNATELY, NO.
UM...

14:04.711 --> 14:05.845
THE FIRST YEAR OF THE PROGRAM,
YOU KNOW,

14:05.879 --> 14:08.915
YOU HAVE TO LOCK THE BOOZE AWAY,
PUT THE BOOTY ON LAYAWAY.

14:08.948 --> 14:09.916
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:09.949 --> 14:10.917
GOOD.

14:10.950 --> 14:11.985
I HAVE
SUCH A TERRIBLE HABIT

14:12.018 --> 14:13.453
OF JUST JUMPING
INTO BED WITH GUYS

14:13.486 --> 14:17.090
AND HAVING WILD,
ORGAZMO, TOE-CURLING,

14:17.123 --> 14:20.260
MAKE-YOU-WANT-TO-CRY SEX.

14:20.293 --> 14:23.930
FRANKLY, I'M RELIEVED.
TO BEING FRIENDS.

14:23.963 --> 14:25.932
AMIGOS.

14:25.965 --> 14:29.135
SO, WHY<i>ARE</i>WE HERE?

14:29.169 --> 14:31.671
FIRST OF ALL,
I JUST WANTED TO APOLOGIZE

14:31.705 --> 14:33.640
FOR OVERREACTING
AT THE SHOOT.

14:33.673 --> 14:34.641
I HAVE A CERTAIN PERSONA,

14:34.674 --> 14:37.644
AND I KNOW THAT YOU WERE
JUST ROLLING WITH THAT.

14:37.677 --> 14:40.647
BUT I'M TRYING TO GET RID OF
THE MYTH OF T.K. THE TERRIBLE,

14:40.680 --> 14:41.781
YOU KNOW?

14:41.815 --> 14:46.119
EMERGE FROM THE CHRYSALIS
A NEW BUTTERFLY, IF YOU WILL.

14:46.152 --> 14:47.253
OH, RIGHT.

14:47.287 --> 14:50.724
WELL, I'M TRYING TO EMERGE
FROM THE HOT MESS OF THIS

14:50.757 --> 14:53.226
TO THE TRIUMPHANT
TEAM OWNER.

14:53.259 --> 14:55.729
PROVE TO THE OLD GUYS
THAT I CAN DO IT.

14:55.762 --> 15:00.233
TELL YOU WHAT --
YOU SUPPORT MY METAMORPHOSIS,

15:00.266 --> 15:01.735
I'LL SUPPORT YOURS,

15:01.768 --> 15:05.739
TO THE TEAM AND ANYBODY ELSE
WHO DARES QUESTION YOU.

15:05.772 --> 15:07.674
I SCRATCH YOUR BACK,
YOU SCRATCH MINE?

15:07.707 --> 15:10.977
ALL THOSE HARD-TO-REACH PLACES.
BUT WITH CLOTHES ON.

15:15.015 --> 15:16.983
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

15:17.017 --> 15:19.319
* YOU TASTE LIKE

15:19.352 --> 15:21.721
* BITTER SUGAR

15:21.755 --> 15:22.722
[ CHEERING ]

15:22.756 --> 15:25.725
* WE'RE DOING ALL RIGHT

15:25.759 --> 15:32.999
* JUST LIKE BITTER SUGA-A-A-R

15:33.033 --> 15:34.701
COME ON!

15:34.734 --> 15:39.139
* LET ME FIX YA

15:39.172 --> 15:41.007
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]
ALL RIGHT!

15:41.041 --> 15:43.009
THANK YOU.

15:43.043 --> 15:46.713
IT'S GREAT TO BE BACK
WHERE IT ALL STARTED FOR US.

15:46.746 --> 15:50.050
VON DOZER! WHOO!

15:51.284 --> 15:54.721
THANK YOU. I WILL, UH,
ADD THESE TO MY COLLECTION.

15:54.754 --> 15:56.322
[ LAUGHTER ]

15:58.391 --> 16:01.361
DO YOU KNOW
"YOU SHOULD BE MINE"?

16:01.394 --> 16:02.762
OH, YEAH.

16:02.796 --> 16:05.265
E-FLAT.

16:05.298 --> 16:07.033
NOW WE'D LIKE TO DO A SONG

16:07.067 --> 16:11.037
THAT'S PROBABLY WON US
MORE AWARDS THAN ANY OTHER,

16:11.071 --> 16:15.809
BUT ONE
WE VERY RARELY PLAY LIVE.

16:15.842 --> 16:18.211
THERE'S A TIME
FOR EVERYTHING.

16:18.244 --> 16:20.747
DAVID.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:22.082 --> 16:23.149
DON'T DO THIS, MAN.

16:23.183 --> 16:27.754
THERE'S LIKE NINE PEOPLE HERE,
BRO. PLAY THE SONG.

16:29.356 --> 16:33.126
* I KEEP LOOKING FOR MY LIFE

16:35.462 --> 16:39.766
* IN MY EYES,
IT HAS BEEN STOLEN *

16:41.868 --> 16:47.841
* ALL THE DAYS THAT PASS ME BY

16:47.874 --> 16:51.111
* KEEP MY SIGHT

16:51.144 --> 16:54.848
* CLEAR AS THE LIGHT

16:54.881 --> 17:00.820
* SOMETIMES IT'S HARD
TO FIND THE MEANING *

17:00.854 --> 17:03.123
* IN A WORLD
THAT'S RUNNING OUT OF TIME *

17:03.156 --> 17:06.459
SCREW YOU, DAVID!
* GIVE ME A SIGN

17:06.493 --> 17:10.463
* 'CAUSE I MAY LOSE MY WAY

17:10.497 --> 17:13.466
* BUT I'M STANDING HERE TO SAY

17:13.500 --> 17:17.404
* THAT YOU SHOULD BE MI-I-I-NE

17:23.810 --> 17:25.245
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:25.278 --> 17:26.813
HERE WE ARE...

17:26.846 --> 17:28.715
JUST THE TWO OF US.

17:28.748 --> 17:32.786
ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING.

17:32.819 --> 17:35.789
DR. SANTINO...

17:35.822 --> 17:37.323
ARE YOU
TRYING TO SEDUCE ME?

17:37.357 --> 17:39.125
[ LAUGHS ]

17:39.159 --> 17:41.194
I-I HADN'T THOUGHT OF IT.

17:41.227 --> 17:42.262
I WISH YOU WOULD.

17:42.295 --> 17:44.164
REALLY?

17:44.197 --> 17:45.365
OH!

17:46.866 --> 17:48.301
[ MOANS ]

17:53.173 --> 17:54.808
OH!

17:54.841 --> 17:57.711
YOU KNOW
THIS ISN'T A SEX DREAM, RIGHT?

17:57.744 --> 18:01.147
I DO KNOW,
AND I DON'T CARE.

18:01.181 --> 18:04.184
[ MOANS ]

18:05.952 --> 18:08.254
WHAT'S HAPPENING RIGHT NOW

18:08.288 --> 18:11.558
BETWEEN THE TWO OF YOU
IS NOT ABOUT SEX.

18:11.591 --> 18:13.326
IT WON'T BE
IF YOU KEEP INTERRUPTING.

18:13.360 --> 18:15.228
[ LAUGHS ]

18:15.261 --> 18:18.732
MY POINT IS...

18:18.765 --> 18:20.834
THERE'S MORE MEANING
BEHIND THIS WHOLE THING.

18:20.867 --> 18:23.336
WHY?
WHY CAN'T I JUST HAVE FUN?

18:23.370 --> 18:24.838
WHY DOES EVERYTHING
HAVE TO MEAN SOMETHING?

18:24.871 --> 18:29.743
WHY CAN'T MY SEX DREAM
JUST BE ABOUT SEX?!

18:32.846 --> 18:34.814
FINE.

18:34.848 --> 18:37.417
WHAT'S IT ABOUT?

18:40.353 --> 18:43.156
ABOUT WANTING
WHAT YOU CAN'T HAVE.

18:46.459 --> 18:47.794
OOH! NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!
DON'T GO!

18:47.827 --> 18:49.796
THAT DOESN'T MEAN GO!
NO!

18:49.829 --> 18:51.831
I...
[ WHIMPERS ]

18:51.865 --> 18:53.299
OKAY.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.870
BUT...WHERE'D EVERYBODY GO?

18:56.903 --> 18:57.971
[ SIGHS ]

18:58.004 --> 19:01.341
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO
HAVE A SEX DREAM WITH NO SEX?!

19:01.374 --> 19:03.810
O-O-OKAY,
SO IN THE LATEST DREAM,

19:03.843 --> 19:06.446
THE SEX WAS WITH MATT
IN "THE GRADUATE."

19:06.479 --> 19:07.847
NO. NO, NO, NO.

19:07.881 --> 19:12.352
IT -- IT WAS STILL
WITH NICO, BUT...

19:12.385 --> 19:14.354
THAT'S THE POINT.

19:14.387 --> 19:17.857
I...WAS MRS. ROBINSON, AND NICO
REPRESENTED WHAT I CAN'T HAVE,

19:17.891 --> 19:20.627
OR SHOULDN'T HAVE.

19:20.660 --> 19:21.528
AND MATT...

19:21.561 --> 19:24.964
WELL, I CAN'T HAVE MATT
ANYMORE ANYWAY.

19:24.998 --> 19:27.967
OR SHOULDN'T HAVE,
RIGHT?

19:28.001 --> 19:29.102
IT WAS MATT WHO TOLD YOU

19:29.135 --> 19:32.939
THIS WAS ABOUT WANTING
WHAT YOU CAN'T HAVE, CORRECT?

19:32.972 --> 19:35.241
DAMN IT!

19:35.275 --> 19:37.977
AND SINCE YOU ARE
THE AUTHOR OF YOUR DREAMS,

19:38.011 --> 19:39.379
WHO DID MATT REPRESENT?

19:39.412 --> 19:42.315
ME.

19:42.349 --> 19:47.020
SO YOU THINK IT'S ALL ABOUT
WANTING WHAT YOU CAN'T HAVE.

19:47.053 --> 19:53.259
SO, DANIELLE, WHAT IS IT
YOU FEEL YOU CAN'T HAVE?

20:00.967 --> 20:02.335
BREAK!
BREAK!
BREAK!

20:03.536 --> 20:05.305
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]
HELLO, COACH.

20:05.338 --> 20:07.474
HEY.

20:07.507 --> 20:08.875
UM, SO, I'VE MADE A DECISION,
AND I WOULD LIKE...

20:08.908 --> 20:10.510
FIRST YOU TAKE MY ADVICE,

20:10.543 --> 20:12.479
THEN YOU TAKE
CREDIT FOR MY ADVICE,

20:12.512 --> 20:14.347
AND THEN
YOU TAKE MY SPOTLIGHT.

20:14.381 --> 20:16.416
GOT TO LEARN
HOW TO GIVE, SON.

20:16.449 --> 20:18.418
YOU GIVE,
AND YOU SHALL RECEIVE.

20:18.451 --> 20:19.319
WELL, SEEING AS THAT

20:19.352 --> 20:21.521
I'M THE NUMBER-ONE RECEIVER
ON THIS TEAM,

20:21.554 --> 20:23.423
I DON'T THINK
I'M THE ONE THAT NEEDS LESSONS.

20:23.456 --> 20:24.424
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

20:24.457 --> 20:26.426
THANK YOU.

20:26.459 --> 20:28.928
FIRST-TEAM OFFENSE,
LET'S GO!

20:28.962 --> 20:31.431
NOT YOU, SON.

20:31.464 --> 20:33.333
UH,
I NEED T.K. OUT THERE.

20:33.366 --> 20:35.001
UH, WHAT THE HELL?

20:35.035 --> 20:38.471
OUR ILLUSTRIOUS OWNER
HAS MOVED T.K. TO NUMBER ONE.

20:41.007 --> 20:44.377
ALL RIGHT, COME ON, COME ON!
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

20:44.411 --> 20:46.579
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

20:46.613 --> 20:47.714
HEY, MR. HARPER.

20:47.747 --> 20:50.450
YEAH, THIS IS RAY JAY SANTINO
HERE FROM HAWKS CARES.

20:50.483 --> 20:51.351
HOW YOU DOING TODAY?

20:51.384 --> 20:52.986
HARPER: Yeah, I'm doing well,
thank you.

20:53.019 --> 20:54.454
YEAH, WE WERE
JUST HOPING TO COUNT ON YOU

20:54.487 --> 20:57.090
TO MATCH LAST YEAR'S
DONATION OF $1,000.

20:57.123 --> 20:58.425
[ Click, dial tone ]

20:58.458 --> 21:01.528
MR. HARPER?

21:01.561 --> 21:03.463
HELLO, RAY JAY.

21:03.496 --> 21:05.465
YOU ENJOYING THE JOB?

21:05.498 --> 21:08.368
MY MOM SENT YOU HERE
TO CHECK UP ON ME, DIDN'T SHE?

21:08.401 --> 21:10.470
WHAT SHOULD I TELL HER?

21:10.503 --> 21:13.039
TELL HER
EVERYTHING'S GOING GREAT

21:13.073 --> 21:15.475
AND THAT I HAVE
A REAL FUTURE HERE.

21:15.508 --> 21:17.744
[ LAUGHS ]

21:17.777 --> 21:20.013
AND THAT
JULIETTE'S TEACHING ME

21:20.046 --> 21:22.315
A TON OF THINGS
THAT I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT.

21:23.450 --> 21:26.519
YEAH,
LEAVE OUT THAT LAST PART.

21:26.553 --> 21:29.389
SMART.

21:33.026 --> 21:35.995
*<i>BUT I'M STANDING HERE</i>
<i>TO SAY</i>*

21:36.029 --> 21:40.500
*<i>THAT YOU SHOULD</i>
<i>BE MI-I-I-I-NE</i>*

21:40.533 --> 21:42.102
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

21:42.135 --> 21:44.371
TELL ME ABOUT THIS SONG.

21:46.439 --> 21:50.010
THERE'S ALL TYPES OF MYTHS
ABOUT IT --

21:50.043 --> 21:52.012
THAT YOU WOULDN'T
PLAY IT LIVE

21:52.045 --> 21:54.981
BECAUSE IT WAS
ABOUT DAVID'S EX-FIANCÃ©E.

21:55.015 --> 21:56.016
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHICH ONE?

21:56.049 --> 21:57.117
OR DAVID'S DRUG PROBLEM?

21:57.150 --> 21:58.551
David: WHOA,
I DIDN'T HAVE A PROBLEM.

21:58.585 --> 22:01.554
I DID DRUGS,
LIKE EVERY OTHER ROCKER, UM,

22:01.588 --> 22:04.457
INCLUDING
SOMEONE ELSE IN THIS ROOM,

22:04.491 --> 22:06.126
WHO'S SUDDENLY
A FREAKING MONK.

22:06.159 --> 22:07.127
I'M NOT A MONK.

22:07.160 --> 22:09.429
I'M A PARENT WITH
RESPONSIBILITIES NOW, DAVID.

22:09.462 --> 22:10.663
I'M SORRY
IF THAT PISSES YOU OFF!

22:10.697 --> 22:13.433
DAVID...UH,

22:13.466 --> 22:16.670
THIS WAS THE ONLY SONG
THAT YOU WROTE SOLO, RIGHT?

22:16.703 --> 22:19.506
YOU REALLY ARE A FAN.

22:19.539 --> 22:22.509
TELL ME
WHAT THIS SONG'S ABOUT.

22:24.177 --> 22:27.147
IT'S ABOUT WILLA, MY WIFE.
[ SCOFFS ]

22:27.180 --> 22:28.515
AH.

22:28.548 --> 22:30.984
PAUL, BROTHER,
WE'VE BEEN OVER THIS.

22:31.017 --> 22:33.453
IT'S NOT ABOUT HER,
YOU NARCISSISTIC --

22:33.486 --> 22:34.354
[ CHUCKLES ] ME?!

22:34.387 --> 22:36.089
YOU HAVEN'T CHANGED
SINCE YOU WERE 17!

22:36.122 --> 22:37.424
WHEN ARE
YOU GONNA GROW UP?!

22:37.457 --> 22:40.527
SO I CAN BE A...
SOCCER DAD LIKE YOU?!

22:40.560 --> 22:42.529
UH,
SPORT SOME SWEET DOCKERS

22:42.562 --> 22:46.066
AND MAYBE DO A LITTLE BACKYARD
COMPOSTING WITH THE KIDS?!

22:46.099 --> 22:47.133
OKAY, HEY, GUYS.

22:47.167 --> 22:50.070
NO AMOUNT OF MONEY
IS WORTH THIS.

22:50.103 --> 22:52.038
[ SIGHS ]

22:52.072 --> 22:53.573
UH, SO, ARE YOU GONNA BAIL
LIKE YOU DID THE FIRST TIME?

22:53.606 --> 22:56.142
I DIDN'T
BAIL ON THE BAND!

22:56.176 --> 22:57.477
YOU GAVE ME NO CHOICE!

22:57.510 --> 23:00.013
YOU WERE HIGH AND DRUNK
ALL THE TIME,

23:00.046 --> 23:02.115
AND WE COULDN'T WRITE A SONG
TO SAVE OUR LIVES!

23:02.148 --> 23:06.119
SO I DECIDED TO SAVE MY LIFE
AND GET OUT BEFORE IT GOT SAD.

23:06.152 --> 23:09.122
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:09.155 --> 23:11.024
IT GOT SAD ANYWAY.

23:12.659 --> 23:15.028
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

23:17.263 --> 23:20.233
WHAT DID YOU DO --
CLEAN HER DOG'S DINGLEBERRIES?

23:20.266 --> 23:21.234
WITH TWEEZERS.

23:21.267 --> 23:23.069
YOU KNOW,
I DIDN'T KNOW I HAD TO

23:23.103 --> 23:25.138
LEARN HOW TO PLAY FOOTBALL
ON A MATTRESS.

23:25.171 --> 23:28.041
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, WOW.

23:28.074 --> 23:30.477
YOU MIGHT NEED TO
LEARN HOW TO PLAY FOOTBALL,

23:30.510 --> 23:31.544
PERIOD, THERE,
TURF TOE.

23:31.578 --> 23:33.546
'CAUSE THEN YOU COULD SEE
THAT SPEED IS DEADLY.

23:33.580 --> 23:34.481
CHECK THIS OUT.

23:37.650 --> 23:39.486
SO FAST, YOU DIDN'T SEE ME
BITCH-SLAP YOU.

23:39.519 --> 23:41.654
SPIN IT HOWEVER YOU WANT.
WE ALL KNOW YOU DIDN'T EARN IT.

23:43.523 --> 23:47.494
YOU CAN'T JUST SWITCH POSITIONS
LIKE YOU'RE CHANGING CLOTHES.

23:47.527 --> 23:50.063
IT UNDERMINES FRONT OFFICE
AND COACHING STAFF.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.065
NOT TO MENTION
IT DAMAGES TEAM MORALE.

23:52.098 --> 23:54.534
ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU
DO IT ON THE FIELD, PUBLICLY.

23:54.567 --> 23:57.771
LOOK,
WE'D RESPECTFULLY ASK YOU

23:57.804 --> 24:00.640
NOT TO MINGLE
WITH THE PERSONNEL.

24:00.674 --> 24:02.642
THEY'RE<i>MY</i>PERSONNEL.

24:02.676 --> 24:05.645
I WILL MINGLE WITH THEM
HOWEVER I SEE FIT.

24:05.679 --> 24:08.214
I OWN THIS TEAM.

24:08.248 --> 24:10.583
I'M SORRY IF YOU DON'T AGREE
WITH MY DECISIONS.

24:10.617 --> 24:14.187
PERHAPS THIS ISN'T THE PLACE
FOR YOU --

24:14.220 --> 24:16.222
ANY OF YOU.

24:21.227 --> 24:24.564
COMPASSION, WAS IT?

24:24.597 --> 24:29.169
YEAH.
YEAH, MAYBE SHE
JUST NEEDS A HUG.

24:34.240 --> 24:37.677
Dani: [ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

24:45.719 --> 24:48.321
"I KEEP LOOKING FOR MY LIFE.

24:48.355 --> 24:52.125
IN MY EYES,
IT HAS BEEN STOLEN."

24:53.727 --> 24:55.228
DAVID.

24:55.261 --> 25:00.266
WHAT IS IT THAT YOU THINK
WAS STOLEN FROM YOU?

25:02.635 --> 25:03.837
OKAY.

25:03.870 --> 25:07.207
YOU WANT REAL?

25:07.240 --> 25:08.708
HERE IT IS.

25:08.742 --> 25:11.644
THE SONG ISN'T ABOUT WILLA,
HIS WIFE.

25:11.678 --> 25:12.812
IT'S ABOUT HIS SON,
DILLON.

25:14.647 --> 25:17.717
EXCEPT...

25:17.751 --> 25:20.587
I THINK DILLON'S MY SON.

25:20.620 --> 25:24.591
I DIDN'T WANT TO
DESTROY THEIR HAPPINESS,

25:24.624 --> 25:26.593
SO I NEVER SAID A WORD.

25:26.626 --> 25:31.598
AND YET,
EVERY DAY SINCE...

25:31.631 --> 25:34.334
YOU HAVE DESTROYED
YOUR OWN.

25:34.367 --> 25:38.271
YOU'RE NOT SURPRISED
BY ANY OF THIS?

25:39.739 --> 25:42.676
[ SIGHS ]

25:42.709 --> 25:45.779
ONE THING
I CAN TELL YOU...

25:45.812 --> 25:49.716
PAUL SURE AS HELL WILL BE
WHEN I FINALLY TELL HIM.

26:01.227 --> 26:02.662
[ HORNS HONKING ]

26:02.696 --> 26:04.397
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:04.431 --> 26:07.200
OH! T.K.!
[ GASPS ]

26:07.233 --> 26:09.703
YOU MADE IT!

26:09.736 --> 26:11.204
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:11.237 --> 26:14.140
LISTEN, UH,
YOU DIDN'T RETURN MY TEXTS.

26:14.174 --> 26:15.342
WHAT --
I HIT YOU BACK.

26:15.375 --> 26:16.409
TO TELL ME
TO MEET YOU AT A BAR,

26:16.443 --> 26:18.945
WHICH IS THE LAST PLACE
I'M TRYING TO BE RIGHT NOW.

26:18.978 --> 26:20.347
OKAY, YOU CAN'T KEEP
DOING WHAT YOU'RE DOING

26:20.380 --> 26:23.350
BECAUSE MY TEAM THINKS
I'M KISSING YOUR ASS.

26:23.383 --> 26:25.118
AND WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THAT?

26:25.151 --> 26:27.320
YOU GOT WHAT YOU WANTED, RIGHT?
BACK ON THE FIELD.

26:27.354 --> 26:29.255
I WANT IT THE RIGHT WAY.

26:29.289 --> 26:31.257
HARD WORK
IS SO OVERRATED.

26:31.291 --> 26:32.292
MAYBE FOR YOU,

26:32.325 --> 26:34.127
BUT I WASN'T BORN WITH
A SILVER SPOON IN MY MOUTH.

26:34.160 --> 26:36.696
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET YOU
TO RELAX, HAVE SOME FUN.

26:36.730 --> 26:40.300
I'M HAVING FUN!
I'M -- THIS IS ME HAVING FUN.

26:40.333 --> 26:42.202
I'M THE CONDUCTOR
ON THE FUN TRAIN.

26:42.235 --> 26:43.303
WHOO-WHOO!

26:43.336 --> 26:44.437
UH-HUH. RIGHT, T.K.

26:44.471 --> 26:48.274
DO YOU WANT SOME ADVICE
FROM SOMEONE WHO'S BEEN THERE?

26:48.308 --> 26:50.377
I KNOW YOU'RE TRYING TO
CHANGE YOUR IMAGE,

26:50.410 --> 26:54.147
BUT DON'T THROW THE OLD T.K.
OUT WITH THE BATHWATER.

26:54.180 --> 26:58.852
YOU ARE A EXTREMELY DYNAMIC
AND...

26:58.885 --> 27:00.220
REALLY SEXY.

27:00.253 --> 27:01.721
...REALLY SEXY MAN.

27:01.755 --> 27:02.922
[ LAUGHS ]

27:02.956 --> 27:06.393
AND YOU DON'T WANT TO TRADE
THAT IN FOR A LESSER MODEL.

27:06.426 --> 27:09.262
JUST FINE-TUNE IT A BIT.

27:09.295 --> 27:10.764
ROTATE THE TIRES.

27:10.797 --> 27:12.766
PUT A LITTLE OIL
IN YOUR ENGINE.

27:12.799 --> 27:13.700
VROOM!

27:13.733 --> 27:15.835
AND TAKE YOUR FOOT
OFF THE EMERGENCY BRAKE.

27:15.869 --> 27:18.171
YOU'RE LIKE ME, T.K. --
PASSIONATE, INTENSE.

27:18.204 --> 27:20.006
IF WE DON'T
BLOW OFF SOME STEAM,

27:20.040 --> 27:21.808
WE'LL GO
INSANE IN THE MEMBRANE.

27:23.410 --> 27:25.278
YOU KNOW WHAT --
SCREW IT, YEAH.

27:25.311 --> 27:26.279
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

27:26.312 --> 27:27.447
WHO WANTS TO
DO SHOTS OFF MY ABS?

27:27.480 --> 27:29.349
[ WOMEN CHEER ]

27:29.382 --> 27:31.851
WHOO! IT'S SPRING BREAK
UP IN HERE! YEAH, YEAH!

27:33.787 --> 27:37.457
I KNOW YOU THINK
THIS SONG IS ABOUT WILLA AND ME.

27:37.490 --> 27:43.263
BUT...IT ISN'T.

27:43.296 --> 27:44.698
[ SIGHS ]

27:50.403 --> 27:52.339
I THINK DILLON IS MINE.

27:52.372 --> 27:55.442
NO. HE'S NOT.

27:55.475 --> 27:57.877
DUDE.

27:57.911 --> 28:00.280
I KNOW IT MUST BE HARD
FOR YOU TO HEAR,

28:00.313 --> 28:03.483
BUT BASIC MATH TELLS ME --
DAVID.

28:03.516 --> 28:06.052
YOU'RE RIGHT.
DILLON IS NOT MY SON.

28:06.086 --> 28:09.255
BUT HE'S NOT YOURS,
EITHER.

28:11.358 --> 28:14.361
YOU KNOW, I KNEW YOU
SLEPT WITH WILLA, SO I CHECKED.

28:14.394 --> 28:16.496
I DID AN ONLINE DNA TEST.

28:16.529 --> 28:18.365
IT WASN'T HARD.
YOU'RE LIKE A BIG DAMN DOG.

28:18.398 --> 28:20.900
YOU SHED YOUR HAIR
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

28:22.435 --> 28:24.938
THEN WHOSE SON IS HE?

28:24.971 --> 28:28.942
SOME ROADIE.
HE SPLIT.

28:28.975 --> 28:31.511
LOOK, I RAISED HIM.
I'M HIS DAD.

28:34.481 --> 28:38.351
SO...

28:38.385 --> 28:41.855
WHERE DO WE GO FROM HERE,
GENTLEMEN?

28:44.591 --> 28:46.893
T.K.: THIS IS BASURAL.

28:46.926 --> 28:48.395
I'M CLEANER
THAN A BRAZILIAN BIKINI WAX.

28:48.428 --> 28:50.430
WELL, THEN,
IT SHOULDN'T BE A PROBLEM.

28:50.463 --> 28:52.265
IT'S A PROBLEM
'CAUSE I'M OFFENDED.

28:52.298 --> 28:53.500
WERE YOU OUT PARTYING
LAST NIGHT?

28:53.533 --> 28:54.934
SOMEBODY TOLD YOU THAT?

28:54.968 --> 28:55.802
WERE YOU OR WERE YOU NOT

28:55.835 --> 28:57.537
OUT IN A CLUB
WITH JULIETTE PITTMAN?

28:57.570 --> 28:59.272
JULIETTE PITTMAN
TOLD YOU THAT?

28:59.305 --> 29:00.373
IT WASN'T JULIETTE.

29:00.407 --> 29:04.577
THIS FOOT-FUNGUS-HAVING
MOTHER...

29:04.611 --> 29:06.846
TOES IS A LIAR!

29:06.880 --> 29:08.348
WELL, THEN,
TAKE THE TEST,

29:08.381 --> 29:11.284
WHICH YOU'RE CONTRACTUALLY
OBLIGATED TO DO.

29:11.317 --> 29:13.453
TAKE IT. PASS IT.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

29:17.891 --> 29:20.427
YOU SHOULDN'T LISTEN TO RUMORS,
MATTY "D."

29:20.460 --> 29:23.463
[ CHUCKLES ]
COME ON.

29:23.496 --> 29:24.531
RUMORS
CAN BE HELPFUL, "T."

29:24.564 --> 29:26.833
LETS YOU KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON
BEHIND YOUR BACK.

29:30.904 --> 29:33.139
YOU GOT SOMETHING TO ASK ME,
MATT?

29:33.173 --> 29:35.842
YOU HAVE SOMETHING
TO TELL ME, NICO?

29:35.875 --> 29:38.445
NO.

29:43.917 --> 29:44.884
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:44.918 --> 29:46.886
HEY.
IS DAVID HERE?

29:46.920 --> 29:47.821
NO. COME IN.

29:47.854 --> 29:49.856
[ SIGHS ] HE DIDN'T
SHOW UP FOR SOUND CHECK.

29:49.889 --> 29:52.359
CONCERT'S TOMORROW.
I HAVE NO IDEA WHERE THE GUY IS.

29:52.392 --> 29:54.527
[ SIGHS ] WHAT HAPPENED
AFTER YOU LEFT HERE?

29:54.561 --> 29:56.629
HE GOT REAL QUIET.
DIDN'T WANT TO TALK.

29:56.663 --> 29:58.398
SO I-I JUST LET IT BE.

29:58.431 --> 30:01.935
AND THEN AN HOUR AGO,
I GET THIS MESSAGE.

30:01.968 --> 30:05.605
David:<i>HEY, BUDDY.</i>
<i>HOW'S IT GOING?</i>

30:05.638 --> 30:07.440
<i>PERSONALLY,</i>
<i>I'M GOING TO HELL.</i>

30:07.474 --> 30:08.274
[<i>LAUGHS</i>]

30:08.308 --> 30:11.177
<i>DON'T THINK</i>
<i>I'LL MAKE IT OVER.</i>

30:11.211 --> 30:14.447
<i>I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW</i>
<i>I'M SORRY, PAUL.</i>

30:14.481 --> 30:17.350
[<i>SIGHS</i>]
<i>I'M SO DAMN SORRY.</i>

30:18.651 --> 30:22.055
HE'S NEVER DONE THAT BEFORE --
APOLOGIZED.

30:22.088 --> 30:23.556
DO YOU HAVE
A WAY OF TRACKING HIM DOWN?

30:23.590 --> 30:25.525
[ SIGHS ]

30:25.558 --> 30:27.861
LET'S START WITH THE OBVIOUS.
COME ON.

30:29.496 --> 30:32.665
Toes:
WHAT'S UP, TERRENCE?

30:32.699 --> 30:34.901
YOU HAVE A GOOD TIME
LAST NIGHT, BRO?

30:34.934 --> 30:36.536
YOU SCARED?

30:36.569 --> 30:39.372
WHAT -- OF YOU?
HMM?

30:39.406 --> 30:41.441
THAT'S WHY YOU SNITCHED.

30:41.474 --> 30:43.543
THIS ISN'T THE HOOD, T.K.
I DIDN'T SNITCH.

30:43.576 --> 30:47.447
I WENT TO THE MANAGEMENT ABOUT
A CONCERN REGARDING A CO-WORKER.

30:47.480 --> 30:48.682
JUST BEING A GENTLEMAN.

30:48.715 --> 30:50.383
NO,
YOU'RE BEING A LIAR.

30:50.417 --> 30:53.453
AH, SEE, IF YOU SEE
AN ADDICT FALLING OFF THE WAGON,

30:53.486 --> 30:54.954
IT'S NOT REALLY LYING.

30:54.988 --> 30:56.423
IT IS WHEN YOU KNOW

30:56.456 --> 30:59.025
I DIDN'T TOUCH A SIP OF ALCOHOL
LAST NIGHT.

30:59.059 --> 30:59.959
LOOK, I GET IT.

30:59.993 --> 31:02.629
BEING AN ADDICT,
THAT IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

31:02.662 --> 31:04.664
IT'S --
IT'S HEREDITARY, RIGHT?

31:04.698 --> 31:08.568
SO, WE SHOULD JUST BLAME
YOUR CRACKHEAD MAMA.

31:08.601 --> 31:09.602
[ SCOFFS ]

31:09.636 --> 31:12.505
OH, MAN, DON'T BE MAD AT ME,
T.K.

31:12.539 --> 31:15.475
BE MAD AT YOUR MAMA, MAN!

31:15.508 --> 31:17.577
SHE THE ONE THAT LEFT YOUR ASS
IN THE TRASH!

31:24.751 --> 31:27.554
STAY BY THE CAR,
AND I'LL CHECK INSIDE.

31:28.555 --> 31:30.990
David: YO!
JESUS.

31:31.024 --> 31:34.461
DID SOMEBODY LOSE
A MIDDLE-AGED ROCK STAR?

31:34.494 --> 31:36.429
COME ON, MAN!

31:36.463 --> 31:38.932
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
JUST COME DOWN.

31:47.040 --> 31:49.609
WHOOPSIE!

31:49.642 --> 31:52.278
WHOO!

31:52.312 --> 31:53.546
THAT WOULD HAVE HURT.

31:53.580 --> 31:55.515
DAVID, LOOK,
I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET.

31:55.548 --> 31:57.517
JUST COME DOWN,
AND LET'S TALK.

31:57.550 --> 32:00.520
LESS TALK,
MORE ROCK, BABY.

32:00.553 --> 32:01.521
WHOA!

32:01.554 --> 32:02.722
COME ON, BUDDY.

32:02.756 --> 32:04.724
JUST --
JUST COME ON DOWN.

32:11.598 --> 32:14.501
OKAY.

32:14.534 --> 32:17.003
I'M COMING DOWN.

32:23.343 --> 32:24.477
OH, MY GOD!

32:31.317 --> 32:33.520
OH, CRAP. THAT HURTS.

32:33.553 --> 32:35.055
OHH!
YOU CRAZY SON OF A BITCH!

32:35.088 --> 32:36.756
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE DEAD.

32:36.790 --> 32:40.060
UNFORTUNATELY, NO.

32:40.093 --> 32:44.030
THAT --
THAT WAS A BAD IDEA.

32:44.064 --> 32:46.499
NOT YOUR FIRST ONE.

32:46.533 --> 32:48.568
DON'T MOVE, OKAY, BECAUSE YOU
MIGHT HAVE BROKEN SOMETHING.

32:48.601 --> 32:50.704
GO CALL 911.
I'M FINE.

32:50.737 --> 32:52.706
OH, OH, OH.
SORT OF.

32:52.739 --> 32:56.142
DAVID,
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

32:56.176 --> 33:00.547
I WANTED TO...TO GO OUT
IN A DAVID BLAIZE OF GLORY,

33:00.580 --> 33:05.552
LIKE HENDRIX AND MORRISON
AND JOPLIN.

33:05.585 --> 33:08.555
[ LAUGHS ]

33:08.588 --> 33:10.590
I CAN'T
EVEN DO THAT RIGHT.

33:12.492 --> 33:13.760
[ SIGHS ]

33:13.793 --> 33:18.064
ALL THESE YEARS...

33:18.098 --> 33:20.834
I TOLD MYSELF
THIS STORY --

33:20.867 --> 33:25.305
THAT DILLON WAS<i>MY</i>KID,
THAT PAUL STOLE<i>MY</i>LIFE.

33:25.338 --> 33:29.309
THINKING
I HAD A KID OUT THERE

33:29.342 --> 33:33.847
MADE ME FEEL
LIKE I HAD SOMETHING.

33:33.880 --> 33:37.851
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,
I GOT NOTHING.

33:37.884 --> 33:43.757
BUT, DAVID,
YOU ARE STILL WILDLY TALENTED.

33:43.790 --> 33:48.628
YOU ARE STILL
FILLED WITH POSSIBILITIES.

33:48.661 --> 33:52.632
AND IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO INVEST IN THAT STORY.

33:55.669 --> 33:58.171
PARAMEDICS
ARE ON THEIR WAY.

33:58.204 --> 33:59.873
I'M FINE.

33:59.906 --> 34:01.541
OH, OH, OH.

34:01.574 --> 34:04.177
YEAH, MAYBE I SHOULD
KICK YOUR ASS!

34:04.210 --> 34:05.679
YOU SCARED
THE HELL OUT OF ME!

34:05.712 --> 34:09.683
YOU COULDN'T KICK MY ASS
IF YOU TRIED.

34:09.716 --> 34:11.584
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

34:11.618 --> 34:12.886
I CAN AND I HAVE.

34:12.919 --> 34:15.855
SENIOR YEAR -- AFTER PROM.

34:15.889 --> 34:17.891
THAT WHOLE THING
WITH DEB FLORENTINE.

34:17.924 --> 34:20.593
OH, YEAH, SHE WAS WEARING
THAT SMOKING-HOT DRESS.

34:20.627 --> 34:22.796
YEAH,
SHE WAS ALSO MY DATE.

34:22.829 --> 34:24.698
[ SIGHS ]

34:24.731 --> 34:26.700
YOU'RE SUCH
A SON OF A BITCH.

34:26.733 --> 34:27.767
I KNOW.

34:27.801 --> 34:30.904
I KNOW.

34:30.937 --> 34:34.207
[ SIGHS ]

34:36.409 --> 34:38.645
I KNOW.

34:40.780 --> 34:41.781
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:46.786 --> 34:51.558
MATT, PLEASE,
PLEASE TAKE ME WITH YOU.

34:51.591 --> 34:52.625
NO.

34:52.659 --> 34:55.562
I'M GOING TO MY OFFICE,
WHERE I CAN FIND SOME PEACE.

34:55.595 --> 34:58.565
CAN'T YOU
UNDERSTAND THAT?
NO!

34:58.598 --> 35:00.400
I ONLY KNOW
THAT I LOVE YOU!

35:00.433 --> 35:01.835
WELL,
THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

35:01.868 --> 35:03.403
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS ]

35:03.436 --> 35:06.573
[ CRIES ]
MATT, MATT!

35:08.775 --> 35:12.946
BUT, MATT,
WHERE WILL I GO?

35:12.979 --> 35:14.948
WHAT WILL I DO?

35:14.981 --> 35:17.617
FRANKLY, MY DEAR,
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN.

35:17.650 --> 35:21.821
[ CRIES ]

35:21.855 --> 35:29.229
MY DREAMS --
THEY'RE ALL MOVIE REENACTMENTS.

35:29.262 --> 35:31.431
WHAT THE HECK
IS THAT ABOUT?

35:31.464 --> 35:35.201
UM, YOU KNOW, MOVIES
ARE THE MODERN-DAY MYTH.

35:35.235 --> 35:39.773
THEY'RE THE CAMPFIRES WE GATHER
AROUND TO PASS ALONG LEGENDS.

35:39.806 --> 35:41.975
BUT TELL ME THIS.

35:42.008 --> 35:45.779
WHAT DO THESE PARTICULAR MOVIES
ALL HAVE IN COMMON --

35:45.812 --> 35:49.816
"TITANIC," "GRADUATE,"
"GONE WITH THE WIND"?

35:49.849 --> 35:54.220
THEY'RE ALL...
LOVE STORIES.

35:54.254 --> 35:56.856
YEAH, AND?

35:56.890 --> 36:01.661
THEY'RE ALL
TRAGIC LOVE STORIES.

36:01.695 --> 36:07.267
SO, DANIELLE, DO YOU BELIEVE
IN HAPPILY EVER AFTER?

36:07.300 --> 36:09.736
FOR ME?

36:14.374 --> 36:18.645
I'M NOT SO SURE.

36:20.380 --> 36:22.916
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
TO THE SERENITY PRAYER?

36:22.949 --> 36:26.019
I HAD THE COURAGE
TO REARRANGE TOE'S FACE.

36:26.052 --> 36:29.022
SERIOUS QUESTION.

36:29.055 --> 36:32.726
HOW MANY CHANCES DO YOU
EXPECT ME TO KEEP GIVING YOU?

36:32.759 --> 36:33.827
LOOK, I'M SORRY --

36:33.860 --> 36:35.662
YEAH, YOU SURE
AS HELL ARE SORRY.

36:36.863 --> 36:40.266
TOES CALLS MY MOTHER
A CRACK WHORE.

36:42.869 --> 36:45.038
I'M JUST SUPPOSED TO
SMILE AND TAKE THAT?

36:45.071 --> 36:47.007
YOU PUNCHED HIM
IN THE FACE.

36:47.040 --> 36:49.909
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU WANT PEOPLE

36:49.943 --> 36:52.345
TO STOP TREATING YOU
LIKE A PROBLEM CHILD,

36:52.379 --> 36:54.347
STOP CAUSING PROBLEMS.

36:54.381 --> 36:56.349
AND STOP BEING A CHILD.

36:56.383 --> 36:58.051
THEN WHERE WOULD I BE?

36:58.084 --> 36:59.919
YOU'D BE
PLAYING THIS SUNDAY!

36:59.953 --> 37:04.324
INSTEAD,
YOU'RE BENCHED, AGAIN.

37:04.357 --> 37:08.695
I SEE IT REALLY DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT I SAY OR WHAT I DO.

37:08.728 --> 37:12.799
YOU'RE JUST GONNA KEEP SEEING ME
FOR THE PERSON THAT I WAS,

37:12.832 --> 37:16.970
NOT THE GUY I'M TRYING
REALLY HARD TO BE.

37:31.751 --> 37:32.852
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:36.056 --> 37:37.090
WHAT ARE WE CELEBRATING?

37:37.123 --> 37:38.091
TUESDAY.

37:38.124 --> 37:40.427
OH.
OH.

37:40.460 --> 37:42.429
I FEEL A LECTURE
COMING ON.

37:42.462 --> 37:43.997
I'M GONNA BE BRIEF.

37:44.030 --> 37:46.099
YES.
DEFINITELY A LECTURE.

37:46.132 --> 37:48.335
JUST A LITTLE SOMETHING
ABOUT YOUR DAD --

37:48.368 --> 37:50.437
THE UBER-COMPETITIVE
MARSHALL PITTMAN.

37:50.470 --> 37:55.008
IT DIDN'T MATTER WHETHER
HE WAS WATCHING OR PLAYING,

37:55.041 --> 37:56.443
HE LOVED GAMES.

37:56.476 --> 37:57.911
MORE THAN HUMANS.

37:57.944 --> 38:01.014
PERHAPS, BUT WHAT
HE CAME TO REALIZE WAS...

38:01.047 --> 38:04.351
FOOTBALL MAY BE A GAME,
BUT MANAGING PEOPLE --

38:04.384 --> 38:06.986
REAL PEOPLE --
THAT DEFINITELY IS NOT.

38:07.020 --> 38:10.023
IS THIS ABOUT T.K.
GOING ALI ON TOES?

38:10.056 --> 38:12.125
LOOK, FOOTBALL PLAYERS
NEED AGGRESSION.

38:12.158 --> 38:14.127
HAPPY PLAYERS
DON'T WIN GAMES.

38:14.160 --> 38:17.997
JULIETTE, IF YOU WANT TO
DESTROY YOUR OWN LIFE,

38:18.031 --> 38:19.132
THAT'S YOUR CHOICE.

38:19.165 --> 38:24.137
BUT BEING THE OWNER OF A TEAM,
PEOPLE DEPEND ON YOU.

38:24.170 --> 38:27.774
YOU THINK ABOUT THAT
NEXT TIME YOU MAKE A DECISION.

38:27.807 --> 38:29.009
THINK HARD.

38:29.042 --> 38:30.910
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

38:30.944 --> 38:34.914
GROW UP.

38:36.116 --> 38:38.118
YOU'RE NOT MY FATHER,
NICO!

38:38.151 --> 38:42.122
ALL THESE YEARS --
ACTING LIKE MY GREAT PROTECTOR.

38:42.155 --> 38:44.391
I KNOW
ABOUT YOU AND MY MOTHER.

38:48.828 --> 38:53.900
I HAD A VERY COMPLICATED
RELATIONSHIP WITH YOUR PARENTS.

38:53.933 --> 38:57.404
I CARED ABOUT BOTH OF THEM.

38:57.437 --> 38:59.839
AND I CARE
VERY MUCH ABOUT YOU.

38:59.873 --> 39:01.408
NOW YOU WORK FOR ME.

39:02.442 --> 39:05.178
MAYBE YOU NEED TO
THINK HARD ABOUT THAT.

39:15.922 --> 39:16.623
HEY,
WHO'S READY TO ROCK?!
HEY!

39:17.824 --> 39:18.591
YOU WANT TO COME OUT THERE
WITH US -- SING SOME BACKUP?
OH!

39:18.625 --> 39:19.459
YOU CLEARLY
KNOW ALL THE SONGS.

39:19.492 --> 39:21.728
YOU GUYS DON'T
WANT TO HEAR ME SING.

39:21.761 --> 39:22.829
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

39:22.862 --> 39:24.030
DUDE,
YOU SMELL LIKE WHISKEY.

39:24.064 --> 39:26.833
COLOGNE, MAN!

39:26.866 --> 39:29.969
OKAY, ONE DRINK.
ONE.

39:30.003 --> 39:33.740
ROME WASN'T
BUILT IN A DAY.

39:33.773 --> 39:35.942
SHALL WE ROCK THE HOUSE,
MY GOOD MAN?

39:35.975 --> 39:37.944
WE SHALL!

39:37.977 --> 39:41.748
Man: LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
VON DOZER!

39:41.781 --> 39:43.783
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

39:51.091 --> 39:53.793
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

39:56.996 --> 40:01.735
David: * OH

40:01.768 --> 40:05.071
[ SLOW-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

40:05.105 --> 40:10.076
* GO

40:12.178 --> 40:17.884
* GO ON

40:20.053 --> 40:23.757
* TAKE ME

40:26.593 --> 40:30.030
* FOR A RIDE

40:30.063 --> 40:33.833
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]

40:33.867 --> 40:35.969
Nico:
YOU'RE HERE KIND OF LATE.

40:36.002 --> 40:38.104
AND DRESSED TO ROCK.

40:38.138 --> 40:39.873
I WAS AT A CONCERT.

40:39.906 --> 40:41.107
HMM.

40:41.141 --> 40:44.778
AND, UH,
RAY JAY TEXTED ME,

40:44.811 --> 40:48.982
SAID THAT HE WAS WORKING LATE,
AND I WAS CURIOUS.

40:49.015 --> 40:52.085
HE IS...WORKING LATE.

40:52.118 --> 40:55.021
SO I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO WORRY ABOUT?

40:55.055 --> 40:57.824
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

40:57.857 --> 40:59.859
HE HAS A CRUSH ON HER.

40:59.893 --> 41:01.761
[ SIGHS ]

41:01.795 --> 41:05.832
BUT DOES SHE HAVE
A CRUSH ON HIM BACK?

41:05.865 --> 41:07.834
ONLY IN HIS DREAMS.

41:07.867 --> 41:10.136
AS LONG AS
THEY STAY THERE.

41:16.076 --> 41:19.179
* YEAH, I BELIEVE

41:19.212 --> 41:23.016
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]
* IN THE OTHER

41:23.049 --> 41:27.153
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

41:28.955 --> 41:31.024
ANYTHING GOING ON?

41:31.057 --> 41:35.028
NOTHING'S GOING ON,
DONNALLY...

41:35.061 --> 41:36.963
WITH DANI AND ME.

41:40.333 --> 41:42.202
AND JULIETTE?

41:44.237 --> 41:48.241
SHE'S GOT TO GO.
